The paper deals with type systems and their ability to enforce bounded interactions, which suggests a focus on logic and programming languages. The use of Lafont's soft linear logic and inspiration from recent works on session types as intuitionistic linear logic formulas further supports this. Therefore, likely arXiv CS sub-categories include cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science). Additionally, the paper's focus on session types and interactions suggests a possible fit with cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
